Inheritance:When One Object acquire all the properties and behaviour of parent class

parent -> child
super -> sub
base -> derived

types of inheritance
1)Single
2)Multilevel
3)Multiple -> is not supported in Kotlin

Solution : Interface

4)Hierarchical

5)Hybrid

Java:
class A
{
	void a()
	{

	}
}

Kotlin:
class A
{
	fun a()
	{

	}
}

Java:

interface A
{
	void a();
	
}

Kotlin:
interface A
{
	void a();
	
}

interface A
{
	fun a()
	{
		
	}
	
}



